Should I change this import string somehow? 

@import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@200,300;400;500;700&display=swap");

Yes, there's an issue with the import string. The current format has a mixture of syntax for weight specifications. Here's the corrected version:

```css
@import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@200;300;400;500;700&display=swap");
```

The problem was that you had a comma after 200 and a semicolon after 300. When specifying multiple weights in Google Fonts imports, you should separate each weight with a semicolon (`;`). The corrected version consistently uses semicolons to separate all the font weight values.
